<subSubSection id="40F16570127DFFC9FF62FAA1FD896BEC" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="682" pageId="24" pageNumber="681" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="085436FB127DFFC9FF62FAA1FD896BEC" blockId="24.[151,1127,219,1588]" lastBlockId="25.[113,1089,220,500]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="682" pageId="24" pageNumber="681">
<emphasis id="3A9FEAE9127DFFC8FF62FAA1FE3D6FEC" bold="true" box="[151,400,1403,1427]" pageId="24" pageNumber="681">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="CFEB4D78127DFFC8FE60FAA7FD096FEB" authority="Bílý &amp; Brûlé, 2013" authorityName="Bílý &amp; Brûlé" authorityYear="2013" box="[405,676,1405,1428]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="681" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="purpureiventris" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="3A9FEAE9127DFFC8FE60FAA7FD096FEB" box="[405,676,1405,1428]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="681">Agrilaxia purpureiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="21AC5792127DFFC8FD5CFAA6FD576FEC" box="[681,762,1404,1427]" pageId="24" pageNumber="681" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="CFEB4D78127DFFC8FC63FAA7FBA66FEB" baseAuthorityName="Gory" baseAuthorityYear="1841" box="[918,1035,1405,1428]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="681" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bivittata">
<emphasis id="3A9FEAE9127DFFC8FC63FAA7FBA66FEB" box="[918,1035,1405,1428]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="681">A. bivittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
speciesgroup and it is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="CFEB4D78127DFFC8FE26FA47FD736FCB" authority="(Cobos, 1972)" baseAuthorityName="Cobos" baseAuthorityYear="1972" box="[467,734,1435,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="681" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculata">
<emphasis id="3A9FEAE9127DFFC8FE26FA47FDED6FCB" box="[467,576,1437,1460]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="681">A. oculata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="6C7A4B0A127DFFC8FDB8FA41FD7B6FCB" author="COBOS A." box="[589,726,1435,1460]" pageId="24" pageNumber="681" pagination="5 - 235" refId="ref16965" refString="COBOS A. 1972: Ensayo monografico sobre las Anthaxia Eschs. (Coleoptera, Buprestidae) de America. Tercera parte: Subgenero Agrilaxia Kerremans. Archivos de Instituto de Aclimatacion (Almeria) 16: 5 - 235." type="journal article" year="1972">Cobos, 1972</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="70FC766B127DFFC8FD1EFA41FC836FCC" box="[747,814,1435,1459]" name="Brazil" pageId="24" pageNumber="681">Brasil</collectingCountry>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="CFEB4D78127DFFC8FC92FA47FF616FAB" authority="Obenberger, 1924" authorityName="Obenberger" authorityYear="1924" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="681" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schmidti">
<emphasis id="3A9FEAE9127DFFC8FC92FA47FC706FCB" box="[871,989,1437,1460]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="681">A. schmidti</emphasis>
Obenberger, 1924
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="70FC766B127DFFC8FF2EFA66FEFB6FAC" box="[219,342,1467,1492]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="24" pageNumber="681">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
). It differs from both by less caudiform and more glabrous elytra without any traces of longitudinal carinae. From 
<taxonomicName id="CFEB4D78127DFFC8FDA1FA07FD606F8B" authorityName="Obenberger" authorityYear="1924" box="[596,717,1501,1524]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="681" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schmidti">
<emphasis id="3A9FEAE9127DFFC8FDA1FA07FD606F8B" box="[596,717,1501,1524]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="681">A. schmidti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it differs (except for the distribution) by deeper frontal depression, narrower vertex, form of the pronotal black spots which reach anterior pronotal margin in 
<taxonomicName id="CFEB4D78127DFFC8FE37F9C7FD966C4B" authorityName="Obenberger" authorityYear="1924" box="[450,571,1565,1588]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="681" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schmidti">
<emphasis id="3A9FEAE9127DFFC8FE37F9C7FD966C4B" box="[450,571,1565,1588]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="681">A. schmidti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the shape of golden green circumscutellar triangle which reaches almost one third of elytral length in 
<taxonomicName id="CFEB4D78127CFFC9FD7AFF07FCAA6A8B" authorityName="Obenberger" authorityYear="1924" box="[655,775,221,244]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="682" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schmidti">
<emphasis id="3A9FEAE9127CFFC9FD7AFF07FCAA6A8B" box="[655,775,221,244]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="682">A. schmidti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and by the colouration of the ventral surface (bronze-green with blue-green metepisterna and first laterosternite and purple second laterosternite in 
<taxonomicName id="CFEB4D78127CFFC9FE9AFEC7FE4A6B4B" authorityName="Obenberger" authorityYear="1924" box="[367,487,285,308]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="682" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schmidti">
<emphasis id="3A9FEAE9127CFFC9FE9AFEC7FE4A6B4B" box="[367,487,285,308]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="682">A. schmidti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). From 
<taxonomicName id="CFEB4D78127CFFC9FDCBFEC7FD066B4B" baseAuthorityName="Cobos" baseAuthorityYear="1972" box="[574,683,285,308]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="682" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculata">
<emphasis id="3A9FEAE9127CFFC9FDCBFEC7FD066B4B" box="[574,683,285,308]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="682">A. oculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it differs by the shape of the circumscutellar triangle which is widened towards the humeri in 
<taxonomicName id="CFEB4D78127CFFC9FD10FEE7FCF86B2B" baseAuthorityName="Cobos" baseAuthorityYear="1972" box="[741,853,317,340]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="682" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculata">
<emphasis id="3A9FEAE9127CFFC9FD10FEE7FCF86B2B" box="[741,853,317,340]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="682">A. oculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the longer and more elevate posthumeral carina and by the concolorous lateral part of elytra which bear narrow, golden green, lateral stripe in 
<taxonomicName id="CFEB4D78127CFFC9FE45FEA7FDB06BEB" baseAuthorityName="Cobos" baseAuthorityYear="1972" box="[432,541,381,404]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="682" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculata">
<emphasis id="3A9FEAE9127CFFC9FE45FEA7FDB06BEB" box="[432,541,381,404]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="682">A. oculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="40F16570127CFFC9FF84FE46FB976BAB" pageId="25" pageNumber="682" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="085436FB127CFFC9FF84FE46FB976BAB" blockId="25.[113,1089,220,500]" pageId="25" pageNumber="682">
<emphasis id="3A9FEAE9127CFFC9FF84FE46FF5C6BCB" bold="true" box="[113,241,412,436]" pageId="25" pageNumber="682">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is composed of the Latin adjective 
<emphasis id="3A9FEAE9127CFFC9FCDEFE47FC3A6BCB" box="[811,919,413,436]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="682">purpureus</emphasis>
(purple) and the noun 
<emphasis id="3A9FEAE9127CFFC9FF58FE67FF5D6BAB" box="[173,240,445,468]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="682">venter</emphasis>
(belly) to stress the conspicuous purple colouration of the abdomen; adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
